BMW INTERNATIONAL OPEN
June 24, 2012
Danny Willett
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
 Q.   Congratulations from all of us, it was a tough gig but you got it done.   How did it feel?  
DANNY WILLETT:   It's amazing.   It was a tough day, it brutal; the wind it was whipping and it was raining, and Marcus had a great round today, and I hung in there nicely.   I mean, what was it, the fourth or the fifth playoff hole?   Hopefully gave people a good show, but no, it's brilliant.  
   
 Q.   With 19 top ten's, up there in the winner's frame, must be very exciting for a young man like you.   What sort of work did you have to do, and how did you sleep last night?  
DANNY WILLETT:   Slept all right.   Slept on and off.   This week has been kind of strange.   I've been working really hard with support and had the my family and my girlfriend, and Callaway have been brilliant.   I've had some up‑and‑downs over the last 18 months as everyone knows, but injury‑free now and back to training and playing well.   I would just like to thank everyone back home for the support they have given me.   But keep working at it and hopefully we can do it again.   
   
  
  
  
  
  

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT